1. Users Table

Purpose

The Users table stores customer accounts.
It allows people to register, log in, place orders, and track purchases.
Column
Reason
user_id
Primary key. Gives every user a unique identifier so the system can reference them in other tables such as orders.
username
Used for login and identification inside the platform. Easier for users to remember than an ID number.
email
Contact method and also used for account recovery and login verification. Often required to be unique.
password_hash
Stores the encrypted version of the user password. Storing plain passwords would create a security risk.
first_name
Allows the system to address users personally and store profile information.
last_name
Helps identify the user and is often used for delivery or billing details.
created_at
Records when the account was created. Useful for account management, analytics, and auditing.
account_status
Shows if the account is active, suspended, or disabled. This helps administrators manage misuse or inactive accounts.
2. Producers Table

Purpose

The Producers table stores accounts for businesses or sellers that provide products.
Separating producers from users helps manage sellers independently from customers.
  Column
Reason
producer_id
Primary key. Gives each producer a unique identifier. Other tables reference this ID to link products to the correct producer.
producer_name
Stores the business or brand name shown to customers.
email
Contact method for the producer and also used for login access.
password_hash
Stores the encrypted password for the producer account. Protects login credentials.
phone
Allows direct communication with the producer for support or order issues.
address
Stores the producer’s business location for shipping, records, or verification.
created_at
Records when the producer account was created. Useful for tracking platform growth and account activity.
3. Products Table

Purpose

The Products table stores the items that producers sell.
Each product links to a specific producer so the system knows who owns and supplies the item.
  Column
Reason
product_id
Primary key. Unique identifier for each product.
producer_id
Foreign key linking the product to the producer who sells it. Without this link the system cannot identify the seller.
product_name
The name displayed to customers when browsing products.
description
Stores details about the product such as materials, features, or specifications. Helps customers understand what they are buying.
price
Stores the cost of the product. Required to calculate order totals.
stock_quantity
Tracks how many units are available. Prevents selling products that are out of stock.
created_at
Records when the product was added to the system. Useful for product management and reporting.
4. Orders Table

Purpose

The Orders table records purchases made by users.
It connects customers to the products they buy and tracks the status of the transaction.
  Column
Reason
order_id
Primary key. Unique identifier for each order so it can be tracked and managed.
user_id
Foreign key linking the order to the user who placed it. This allows the system to show order history.
product_id
Foreign key linking the order to the product being purchased. This shows what item was bought.
quantity
Records how many units of the product were ordered.
total_price
Stores the total cost of the order. Useful for reporting and payment records.
order_status
Shows the current state of the order such as pending, shipped, or delivered. Helps with order tracking.
order_date
Records when the order was placed. Used for tracking, analytics, and customer order history.
